The ANC has called on government to establish the veracity of the claims made in the so called #GuptaEmails.On Friday ANC spokesperson Zizi Kodwa said allegations of ministers sharing details of cabinet meetings with private individuals cannot be left unattended as they threaten the integrity and credibility of the state.&#8220;The allegation that certain ministers shared details of cabinet meetings&#8230;on its own is very serious and must be attended to,&#8221;&#8221; That allegation cannot be left unattended because at the heart of these allegations is the integrity and credibility of the democratic state and the democratic state must do everything to defend its integrity,&#8221; said Kodwa.The ANC has also reiterated a call of its National Executive Committee calling for the establishment of a Judicial Commission of Enquiry into allegations of state capture without delay.-TNA Reporter